// useTerminalTabs
// Manages a list of terminal sessions (tabs) for a given project/session, with persistence of the active tab.

The active tab ID is persisted to localStorage under the key "terminal-active-tab:{project}:{session}".
On load, the saved tab is restored if it still exists; otherwise the first tab is selected.
reorderTabs applies an optimistic update and reverts on API failure.

FUNCTION useTerminalTabs({ project, session }) -> UseTerminalTabsReturn         EXPORT
  CALLS: api (api)
  Manages state: tabs, activeTabId, isLoading, error.
  On mount (and when project/session changes), calls refresh to load the terminal session list.

---

FUNCTION refresh()
  CALLS: api (api)
  Fetches the current terminal sessions from the API.
  Restores the active tab from localStorage if the saved ID still exists, or defaults to the first tab.
  On failure, clears tabs and activeTabId.

---

FUNCTION addTab()
  CALLS: api (api)
  Creates a new terminal session via the API, refreshes the tab list, auto-selects the new tab,
  and persists the selection to localStorage.

---

FUNCTION removeTab(id)
  CALLS: api (api)
  Deletes the terminal session via the API, then refreshes the tab list.

---

FUNCTION renameTab(id, name)
  CALLS: api (api)
  Renames the terminal session via the API, then refreshes the tab list.

---

FUNCTION reorderTabs(fromIndex, toIndex)
  CALLS: api (api)
  Validates the indices, applies the reorder optimistically to local state, then calls the API.
  If the API call fails, reverts the local state to the original order.

---

FUNCTION handleSetActiveTab(id)
  Sets the active tab if the given id exists in the current tab list, and persists the selection to localStorage.

---

FUNCTION getStorageKey(project, session) -> string
  Returns the localStorage key used to persist the active tab for a given project and session.
